    <subfield code="y">00009 Caption not extracted</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="856" ind1="4" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="s">15372</subfield>
    <subfield code="u">http://inspirehep.net/record/1335297/files/AxionDifModBoth.png</subfield>
    <subfield code="y">00004 The  average  $\prec{\vec \upsilon} .{\hat n}\succ/\upsilon_0$,  essentially the axion fux in units of $(\rho_a/m_a)\upsilon_0$, as a function of the polar angle $\Theta$. We note that some of the  asymmetry remains. The favored direction is still along the sun's direction of motion (the angles $\Theta=0$, and $\Theta=\pi$ cannot be distinguished).</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="856" ind1="4" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="s">5721</subfield>
    <subfield code="u">http://inspirehep.net/record/1335297/files/AxionTotMod.png</subfield>
    <subfield code="y">00003 The  average $\prec{\vec \upsilon} .{\hat n}\succ/\upsilon_0$,  the  average total axion flux in units $(\rho_a/m_a)\upsilon_0$ as a function of the polar angle $\Theta$. We note the large asymmetry. The favored direction is opposite to the velocity of  the sun's motion ($\Theta=\pi$).</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="856" ind1="4" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="s">6376</subfield>
    <subfield code="u">http://inspirehep.net/record/1335297/files/exactmod.png</subfield>
    <subfield code="y">00001 The  variation of the average axion flux, in units of $(\rho_a/m_a)\upsilon_0$,  due to the motion of the Earth around the sun. As expected,  the maximum occurs when $\alpha=0$ (around June 3nd).</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="856" ind1="4" ind2=" ">
