    <subfield code="y">00005 The average $\prec{\vec \upsilon} .{\hat n}\succ/\upsilon_0$, essentially the average total axion flux in units $(\rho_a/m_a)\upsilon_0$ as a function of the polar angle $\Theta$, when the sense of direction cannot be distinguished. The angles $\Theta=0$, and $\Theta=\pi$ cannot be distinguished. The asymmetry, however, with the $\Theta=\pi/2$ remains.</subfield>
  </datafield>
